Okay so I will periodically flag a place to try in my childhood neighborhood since there has been a little gentrification. And I must say there gave been great finds which has been refreshing to your standard Mickey D's to local Chinese restaurant fare.  So this establishment was next in life to embrace and what a great 1st impression. According to my mom they keep a steady flow of folks especially in the summer.  We did takeout and while waited (which was a little bit), we noticed several things. There is great turnover whether dining in, for takeout or online/call-in orders. Also we found there were two private hibachi rooms in back.  So needless to say the next trip will be to sit in 1st and foremost and to try the hibachi. We ordered......okay I ordered quite a bit (result of running in "E" from just a morning cup of tea).  Either all ordered well at least what was immediately eaten was amazing and super fresh. So I anticipate that when I go back for the leftovers they'll be equally amazing.  Order: fried oysters (good), coconut shrimp (😋😜🤗 #Delish and Oh My Word the sauce), Rainbow roll (standard supa fresh), Caribbean roll (delish), Angry Birds roll (#Yum), Alaskan Roll (Mom liked), Nabe Yaki Udon Noodle Soup Noodle (TO BE EATEN), and Thai ice tea (okay)  So can you tell......one I was super hungry.......two we enjoyed the takeout. So suffice it to say this will be the spot outside of our obsession with Fumo. Pricey but worth it, fresh and great portions.  Side note little pet peeve one of the sushi chefs didn't change gloves while making orders and touching the garage can to toss out debris and didn't rinse out the counter rag often enough between counter wipes.  With that said the food was amazing.
